data.title: BELTCROSS2: Calculate the closest approaches of asteroids to meteoroid streams
data.name: BELTCROSS2
data.description: A computer program calculating the closest approaches of asteroid to the mean orbits of meteoroid streams, new version upploaded on January 15, 2024.

evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "compiled as the static-binary files and have suffix "*.exes". Their"
"The code provided consists of the set of the executable programs."

Descriptions of programs (e.g., moid.exes, relvel.exes, basicdate.exes) show they compute orbital characteristics, MOID, relative velocities, and closest approaches between objects and meteor streams, i.e., domain scientific calculations.
